<tr id="iconRow">
<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Middletone Placement" class="currentChild" href="Middletone_Placement">Middletone Placement</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In <a title="Halftone" href="Halftone">halftone</a> reproduction, a means of determining the sizes of the <a title="Middletone" href="Middletone">middletone</a> dots, accomplished during <a title="Scanner" href="Scanner">scanner</a> set up by indicating the points on the input set up <a title="grayscale" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/grayscale">grayscale</a> where <a title="Shadow" href="Shadow">shadow</a>s, <a title="Diffuse Highlight" href="Diffuse_Highlight">diffuse highlight</a>s, and <a title="Middletone" href="Middletone">middletone</a>s are to lie, to ensure proper <a title="Contrast" href="Contrast">contrast</a> in the final reproduced image. This controls the ultimate sizes of the middletone dots which, if not done properly, results in poor color reproduction. Other factors that must be taken into account during middletone placement are the anticipated <a title="Dot Gain" href="Dot_Gain">dot gain</a> from the printing process and the type of paper to be utilized. Also of importance is the <a title="Screen Ruling" href="Screen_Ruling">screen ruling</a> that will be used to generate the halftone itself. 
</p>
